      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ANNDAR SPIRIT (2) was strongly fancied last time but ran below expectations when fifth (20.87), beaten 11 lengths. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Has ability and looks hard to stop. BROTHER AND ME (1) struggling for winning form, but gets every chance from the inside. Last time finished 4th on May 24 over 350m at this track behind Precious Glow beaten 6 lengths (20.58) in a Maiden. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. RENAE'S VOGUE (7) produced a moderate performance last time when fifth at Gosford over 388m behind Show More (23.18) in a Maiden. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Shapes as one to consider. CHERRY LOLITA (8) cannot be written off despite a miss here at her latest outing.",
